title: For Sale:  Bulgarian AK-74 w/ 200 rounds
postcontent:
Selling my Century Arms Bulgarian AK-74 (5.45x39) - just converted my first Saiga and I have run out of room! I purchased this gun in May and have had a lot of fun with it - I've put roughly 600 rounds down the pipe and it has been a smooth, reliable shooter from round one. Exactly what you'd expect from an AK. I've thoroughly cleaned this gun after every trip to the range - the internals are rust- and corrosion-free, and the exterior shows very little wear and tear.

I did buy the rifle used, but could swear that it had never been fired. The guys at Bill's told me that the original owner had inherited his father's 47 and no longer wanted the 74. I've no idea why - it has been very accurate and (as mentioned) quite reliable. I test ran a 5 MOA red dot on the rifle and was shooting 1" groups at 25 yards, from a hot barrel even (I'll be the first to admit, I'm not a very good shot, so you can probably expect better). 

I'm including the original magazines I received with it (x2 fire-brick Circle-21 mags), a Saiga optic rail that I fitted to the rifle (mounts to the tang and the sight leaf), a UTG 5-position foregrip, the original polymer furniture, a Tufforce quad rail handguard (currently mounted), a Magpul AFG (currently mounted), a Hogue rubber grip (currently mounted), a green NcStar rifle sling (currently mounted), and a rubber recoil buffer (currently installed). I'll be throwing in 200 rounds of TulAmmo hollow points as well.

May be interested in trades - particularly toward a Sig P226/P220 or a Beretta 92FS. Possibly other items - can't hurt to ask!

Gun is spoken for!

Project Appleseed is a 2 day shooting clinic teaching strong fundamentals of Sight Picture, Sight Alignment, Trigger Squeeze and breathing. Bring you, your spouse, your kids, aunt's, uncles, grandparents, grandchildren, neighbor - whoever and learn how to do it.

postcontent:
I will only accept FTF sales with a firearms transfer at your expense.  Email me for more pictures.

Included is the PPS43, 4 x 35 rd magazines, cleaning kit, new buffer pad, authentic russian PPS43 magazine pouch (holds 3 magazines) and oil bottle, cleaning rod/front sight tool.

Specifications and features:
I.O., Inc Polish PPS-43C semi-automatic handgun
7.62x25mm caliber
250mm (9.84") barrel
35 round capacity
200 meters effective range
Weighs 3.67kg (8 pounds) loaded
Weighs 3.04kg (6.70 pounds) unloaded

The PPS-43C (Pistolet-Pulemet Sudaeva, model of 1943 = Sudaev SMG) was born as an answer to the need for a weapon that is more compact and mobile than the PPSh-41, then in use by the Soviet Army. The PPSh-41 was somewhat too long to be used by tank crews and mobile recon groups and paratroopers, so late in 1941, the Red Army issued a request for a new more compact sub machine gun (SMG). The designer Sudaev initially designed his new SMG in 1942, and it was adopted under the designation of PPS-42. The next year he refined the design, and this final model was designated as the PPS-43. This model was manufactured in significant numbers (nearly two million PPS-43 weapons were manufactured between 1943 and 1946). The PPS-43 is sometimes referred to as the best SMG of World War II. After WWII, it was widely exported to pro-Soviet regimes around the world, and widely copied.

I.O. Inc. redesigned this historical firearm to shoot from a closed bolt position. The safety is located at the front of the triggerguard. The receiver and barrel shroud are made from stamped steel. The rear sight is an L-shaped flip type and is marked for 100 and 200 meters, the front sight is a fixed blade type. The barrel is equipped with a simple muzzle brake. This firearm is an ATF approved pistol. The stock has no function and is permanently fixed in its folded position.

This pistol is manufactured at the famed Radom Plant in Poland. All parts and components are new and Polish made.

title: For Sale:  Romanian SAR-1 AK-47
postcontent:
I am selling (really don't want to) my Romanian SAR-1 AK-47.  This AK is sweet.  Nothing but good reviews on this weapon.  Don't mistake this for the crappy WASR-10s out there.  It's rare to find one of these AK's these days.  It has magazine dimples in the receiver (unlike the WASR-10s) so you don't have to worry about magazine wobble.  It also has the side rail mount for optics mounting.

It has a chrome lined barrel (so good if you shoot corrosive ammo).  Included is all that you see: SAR-1, sling, cleaning kit (fits in buttstock), 3 x 30 rd magazines, 1 x 10 rd magazine, UTG quad rail (with 12 rubber rail covers, these are awesome to protect against heat) which replaces with front handguards so you can mount lasers, optics, bipod, whatever, broom handle fore grip, and 100 rounds of silver bear ammo.

You won't find this kinda package anywhere else.  Will only do FTF sales and firearms transfer.  Get it before it's gone!! Great starter kit for the zombie apocalypse enthusiast!!
